args.question: Prepare the data to associate the highest number of three pointers made by players with their nationalities.

xmode.content:
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# Data
players_data = [
    {"player": "Player A", "three_pointers_made": 200, "nationality": "USA"},
    {"player": "Player C", "three_pointers_made": 180, "nationality": "Spain"},
    {"player": "Player B", "three_pointers_made": 150, "nationality": "Canada"}
]

# Extracting the highest number of three-pointers made by players from each nationality
nationality_max = {}
for data in players_data:
    nationality = data["nationality"]
    three_pointers = data["three_pointers_made"]
    if nationality not in nationality_max or three_pointers > nationality_max[nationality]:
        nationality_max[nationality] = three_pointers

# Plotting
nationalities = list(nationality_max.keys())
three_pointers_made = list(nationality_max.values())

plt.figure(figsize=(8, 6))
plt.bar(nationalities, three_pointers_made, color=['blue', 'red', 'green'])
plt.xlabel('Nationality')
plt.ylabel('Three Pointers Made')
plt.title('Highest Number of Three Pointers Made by Players from Each Nationality')
plt.xticks(rotation=45)
plt.tight_layout()

# Save the plot
plt.savefig('/home/ubuntu/workspace/XMODE/Rotowire/experiments/log/10/highest_three_pointers_by_nationality.png')
plt.close()
